<div class="p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-fuchsia-50 dark:from-violet-950 dark:to-fuchsia-950 min-h-screen">
  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="mb-12 text-center">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">
      <%= pathogen_icon(:arrows_down_up, color: :primary, size: :xl, class: "inline mr-3") %>
      Scroll Behavior
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      Dynamic scroll shadows that indicate scrollable content and fixed header/footer positioning.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Scrollable Content Dialog -->
  <div class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-6 flex items-center">
      <%= pathogen_icon(:scroll, color: :primary, class: "mr-3") %>
      Dialog with Scrollable Content
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 p-8">
      <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4">
        When dialog content exceeds the available height, scroll shadows automatically appear to indicate
        there's more content above or below:
      </p>

      <%= render(Pathogen::DialogComponent.new(id: 'scrollable-dialog', size: :medium, dismissible: true)) do |dialog| %>
        <% dialog.with_show_button(scheme: :primary, size: :medium) do %>
          <%= pathogen_icon(:article, color: nil, class: "mr-2 shrink-0") %>
          Open Scrollable Dialog
        <% end %>

        <% dialog.with_header do %>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Terms of Service</h2>
        <% end %>

        <% dialog.with_body do %>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1. Acceptance of Terms</p>
            <p>
              By accessing and using this service, you accept and agree to be bound by the terms
              and provision of this agreement. These terms of service are a legally binding
              agreement between you and the service provider.
            </p>

            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">2. Use License</p>
            <p>
              Permission is granted to temporarily download one copy of the materials on the
              service for personal, non-commercial transitory viewing only. This is the grant
              of a license, not a transfer of title.
            </p>

            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">3. Disclaimer</p>
            <p>
              The materials on the service are provided on an 'as is' basis. The service makes
              no warranties, expressed or implied, and hereby disclaims and negates all other
              warranties including, without limitation, implied warranties or conditions of
              merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement of
              intellectual property or other violation of rights.
            </p>

            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">4. Limitations</p>
            <p>
              In no event shall the service or its suppliers be liable for any damages
              (including, without limitation, damages for loss of data or profit, or due to
              business interruption) arising out of the use or inability to use the materials
              on the service.
            </p>

            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">5. Accuracy of Materials</p>
            <p>
              The materials appearing on the service could include technical, typographical,
              or photographic errors. The service does not warrant that any of the materials
              on its website are accurate, complete or current.
            </p>

            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">6. Links</p>
            <p>
              The service has not reviewed all of the sites linked to its website and is not
              responsible for the contents of any such linked site. The inclusion of any link
              does not imply endorsement by the service of the site.
            </p>

            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">7. Modifications</p>
            <p>
              The service may revise these terms of service for its website at any time without
              notice. By using this website you are agreeing to be bound by the then current
              version of these terms of service.
            </p>

            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">8. Governing Law</p>
            <p>
              These terms and conditions are governed by and construed in accordance with the
              laws and you irrevocably submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in
              that location.
            </p>

            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">9. Privacy Policy</p>
            <p>
              Your use of the service is also governed by our Privacy Policy. Please review
              our Privacy Policy, which also governs the site and informs users of our data
              collection practices.
            </p>
            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Additional Information</p>
            <p>
              Please be aware that continued use of the service following any changes to these terms will constitute your acceptance of such changes.
            </p>

            <p>
              The service strives to provide an accessible and inclusive experience for all users. For more details about our accessibility features, refer to our Terms of Service.
            </p>

            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">10. Contact Information</p>
            <p>
              If you have any questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us at
              support@example.com. We will respond to your inquiry within 48 hours.
            </p>
          </div>
        <% end %>

        <% dialog.with_footer do %>
          <div class="flex justify-end gap-3">
            <%= render Pathogen::Button.new(scheme: :slate, data: { action: 'click->pathogen--dialog#close' }) do %>
              Decline
            <% end %>
            <%= render Pathogen::Button.new(scheme: :primary, data: { action: 'click->pathogen--dialog#close' }) do %>
              Accept Terms
            <% end %>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>

      <div class="mt-4 bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/20 border border-purple-200 dark:border-purple-800 rounded-lg p-3">
        <p class="text-sm text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-200">
          <strong>Try it:</strong> Open the dialog and notice the scroll shadows at top/bottom indicating more content
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- How Scroll Shadows Work -->
  <div class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-6 flex items-center">
      <%= pathogen_icon(:info, color: :primary, class: "mr-3") %>
      How Scroll Shadows Work
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <!-- Visual Indicators -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <%= pathogen_icon(:eye, color: :primary) %>
            Visual Indicators
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">▲</span>
              <span><strong>Top shadow:</strong> Appears when content is scrolled down (more above)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">▼</span>
              <span><strong>Bottom shadow:</strong> Appears when more content exists below</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">✓</span>
              <span><strong>Automatic:</strong> Shadows update dynamically as you scroll</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">✓</span>
              <span><strong>Smooth:</strong> CSS transitions for subtle, professional appearance</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Technical Details -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <%= pathogen_icon(:gear, color: :primary) %>
            Technical Details
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">•</span>
              <span>Header and footer remain fixed during scroll</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">•</span>
              <span>Body content scrolls independently</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">•</span>
              <span><code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-700 rounded text-xs font-mono">updateScrollShadows()</code> method handles logic</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">•</span>
              <span>Called on scroll events and when dialog renders</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Shadow Behavior States -->
  <div class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-6 flex items-center">
      <%= pathogen_icon(:stack, color: :primary, class: "mr-3") %>
      Shadow Behavior States
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <!-- At Top -->
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
        <div class="mb-2 text-center">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900/20 rounded-full">
            <%= pathogen_icon(:arrow_up, color: :primary) %>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white text-center mb-2">At Top</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-center">
          No top shadow<br>
          Bottom shadow visible
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Middle -->
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
        <div class="mb-2 text-center">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900/20 rounded-full">
            <%= pathogen_icon(:arrows_in_line_vertical, color: :primary) %>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white text-center mb-2">Middle</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-center">
          Top shadow visible<br>
          Bottom shadow visible
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- At Bottom -->
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
        <div class="mb-2 text-center">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/20 rounded-full">
            <%= pathogen_icon(:arrow_down, color: :success) %>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white text-center mb-2">At Bottom</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-center">
          Top shadow visible<br>
          No bottom shadow
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Code Example -->
  <div class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-6 flex items-center">
      <%= pathogen_icon(:code, color: :primary, class: "mr-3") %>
      Code Example
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-900 border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 rounded-lg p-4 shadow-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <pre class="text-sm"><code class="text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200"><%%= render Pathogen::DialogComponent.new(id: 'long-content', size: :medium) do |dialog| %>
  <%% dialog.with_header do %>
    &lt;h2&gt;Long Document&lt;/h2&gt;
  <%% end %>

  <%% dialog.with_body do %>
    &lt;!-- Long content here that exceeds available height --&gt;
    &lt;div class="space-y-4"&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;First paragraph...&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Second paragraph...&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;!-- ... many more paragraphs ... --&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Last paragraph...&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  <%% end %>

  <%% dialog.with_footer do %>
    &lt;!-- Footer actions --&gt;
  <%% end %>
<%% end %>

&lt;!-- Scroll shadows appear automatically when content overflows --&gt;</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Quick Tips -->
  <div>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-6 flex items-center">
      <%= pathogen_icon(:lightbulb, color: :warning, class: "mr-3") %>
      Quick Tips
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-lg p-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <%= pathogen_icon(:magic_wand, color: :primary) %>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100 mb-1">Automatic Shadows</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200">Scroll shadows appear automatically - no configuration needed</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/20 border border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 rounded-lg p-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <%= pathogen_icon(:anchor, color: :success) %>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 dark:text-green-100 mb-1">Fixed Header & Footer</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-green-800 dark:text-green-200">Header and footer remain visible while body content scrolls</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-900/20 border border-purple-200 dark:border-purple-800 rounded-lg p-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <%= pathogen_icon(:arrows_clockwise, color: :primary) %>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-purple-900 dark:text-purple-100 mb-1">Dynamic Updates</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-purple-800 dark:text-purple-200">Shadows update in real-time as user scrolls through content</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-lg p-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <%= pathogen_icon(:eye_closed, color: :warning) %>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 dark:text-amber-100 mb-1">No Shadows When Not Needed</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200">If content fits without scrolling, no shadows appear</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
